headline: Amazon's Black Friday sales, Goldman Sachs acquires ETF issuer
summary: Yahoo Finance Senior Producer John Hyland tracks Monday's top-moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Copper (HG=F) hit a record high, while silver (SI=F) continues its record-breaking rally. Goldman Sachs (GS) is acquiring Innovator Capital, an issuer of exchange-traded funds (ETFs), for $2 billion. Amazon's (AMZN) artificial intelligence (AI) chatbot, Rufus, helped drive Black Friday sales, according to data from Sensor Tower. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Goldman Sachs Bets on Active ETFs
summary: Goldman Sachs just announced a purchase of Innovator Capital Management for about $2 billion. The company has a special focus on so-called defined-outcome funds, or buffer funds, which use options contracts to offer investors protection from market downturns while retaining access to some of the gains.
